The paper deals with lower bounds for turnstile streaming algorithms, which are commonly studied in the data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) communities. The paper also discusses heavy hitters, point query, entropy estimation, and moment estimation, which are problems studied in the computational complexity (cs.CC), data mining (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG) communities.
